The paper deals with training deep neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The method proposed in the paper is applied to image classification models (cs.CV), and the authors mention that it can be used for various types of networks, including feedforward, convolutional, and recurrent neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the regularization effect of batch normalization, which is a topic that falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the authors evaluate their method on the ImageNet dataset, which is a popular benchmark for computer vision tasks (cs.CL).
